supportDesc.collation:
The old parchment binding (wrapper) is now part of the text block as fol. Ar-v (title on Ar); the originally first folio with the planisphere is now stored separately; 
                        I10(-1) (ff. 2-10), II 6(+1) (ff. 8-17), III6 (ff. 18-23), IV8 (ff. 24-31), V6 (ff. 32-37), VI8 (ff. 38-45). 
                        There are quiremarks at the start of Germanicus' Aratea (ff. 10-17) as 'I' (further quiremarks on f. 23v 'II', f. 31v 'III' and on f. 37v 'IIII'. This strongly suggests that the two Aratean texts were transmitted separately at least at the beginning.
